We have prepared the modified Ba0.67Sr0.33TiO3 films for potential application in electrically tunable devices. Deposition temperature strongly affects crystalline quality, surface morphology, remanent polarization and dielectric tunability of the BST films. By optimizing deposition temperature, we have obtained the BST film deposited at 700°C with the tunability of 55.40% and the remanent polarization (2P

                        r
                     )=23.87μC/cm2. The high tunability with appropriate dielectric loss makes the BST films a promising material for tunable microwave application.
